The paper focuses on object detection and semantic segmentation using Convolutional Neural Networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel framework for handling these tasks simultaneously, which involves learning from data (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of local top-down modules, which are a type of neural network architecture (cs.NE) and also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in terms of semantic segmentation.
